      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING CRUISE (2) had been racing well prior to his last start seventh at this track following a Grade 5 win three back with a third placing. Safe beginner and drawn well close to the inside. Looks suited here and big improvement expected. KINGSBRAE TED (4) goes very well this course and distance starting 21 times for nine wins and nine minors. In the money last time at this track (17.27) in a NG, finishing a 2.25 lengths second. With even luck and a clean start should be thereabouts. TOMMIE'S BRIDE (7) is a talented type who has been in the money at the last three starts, the latest finishing third (17.55) at this track. Has a good record here including five wins. Best form too dangerous to ignore. Have to include. OVERRIDING (1) was well fancied in betting last start but could only manage a nose away in second (17.37). Overdue and is among the main hopes.",
